  34:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   *** RTC Wakeup configuration ***
  35:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   ================================
  36:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
  37:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) To configure the RTC Wakeup Clock source and Counter use the HAL_RTCEx_SetWakeUpTimer()
  38:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         function. You can also configure the RTC Wakeup timer with interrupt mode
  39:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         using the HAL_RTCEx_SetWakeUpTimer_IT() function.
  40:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) To read the RTC WakeUp Counter register, use the HAL_RTCEx_GetWakeUpTimer()
  41:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         function.
  42:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
  43:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   *** Outputs configuration ***
  44:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   =============================
  45:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]  The RTC has 2 different outputs:
  46:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) RTC_ALARM: this output is used to manage the RTC Alarm A, Alarm B
  47:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         and WaKeUp signals.
  48:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         To output the selected RTC signal, use the HAL_RTC_Init() function.
  49:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) RTC_CALIB: this output is 512Hz signal or 1Hz.
  50:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         To enable the RTC_CALIB, use the HAL_RTCEx_SetCalibrationOutPut() function.
  51:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) Two pins can be used as RTC_ALARM or RTC_CALIB (PC13, PB2) managed on
  52:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         the RTC_OR register.
  53:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) When the RTC_CALIB or RTC_ALARM output is selected, the RTC_OUT pin is
  54:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         automatically configured in output alternate function.
  55:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
  56:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   *** Smooth digital Calibration configuration ***
  57:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   ================================================
  58:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
  59:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) Configure the RTC Original Digital Calibration Value and the corresponding
  60:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         calibration cycle period (32s,16s and 8s) using the HAL_RTCEx_SetSmoothCalib()
  61:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         function.
  62:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
  63:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   *** TimeStamp configuration ***
  64:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   ===============================
  65:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
  66:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) Enable the RTC TimeStamp using the HAL_RTCEx_SetTimeStamp() function.
  67:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         You can also configure the RTC TimeStamp with interrupt mode using the
  68:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         HAL_RTCEx_SetTimeStamp_IT() function.
  69:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) To read the RTC TimeStamp Time and Date register, use the HAL_RTCEx_GetTimeStamp()
  70:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         function.
  71:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
  72:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   *** Internal TimeStamp configuration ***
  73:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   ===============================
  74:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
  75:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) Enable the RTC internal TimeStamp using the HAL_RTCEx_SetInternalTimeStamp() function.
  76:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         User has to check internal timestamp occurrence using __HAL_RTC_INTERNAL_TIMESTAMP_GET_FLAG
  77:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****     (+) To read the RTC TimeStamp Time and Date register, use the HAL_RTCEx_GetTimeStamp()
  78:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****         function.
  79:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
  80:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****    *** Tamper configuration ***
  81:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****    ============================
  82:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****    [..]
  83:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****      (+) Enable the RTC Tamper and configure the Tamper filter count, trigger Edge
  84:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****          or Level according to the Tamper filter (if equal to 0 Edge else Level)
  85:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****          value, sampling frequency, NoErase, MaskFlag,  precharge or discharge and
  86:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****          Pull-UP using the HAL_RTCEx_SetTamper() function. You can configure RTC Tamper
ARM GAS  C:\Users\solar\AppData\Local\Temp\ccl0mnNp.s 			page 3


  87:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****          with interrupt mode using HAL_RTCEx_SetTamper_IT() function.
  88:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****      (+) The default configuration of the Tamper erases the backup registers. To avoid
  89:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****          erase, enable the NoErase field on the RTC_TAMPCR register.
  90:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****      (+) STM32L412xx and STM32L422xx only : With new RTC tamper configuration, you have to call HAL
  91:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****          perform TAMP base address offset calculation.
  92:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****      (+) STM32L412xx and STM32L422xx only : If you don't intend to have tamper using RTC clock, you
  93:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****          by setting ClockEnable inti field to RTC_CLOCK_DISABLE.
  94:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****      (+) STM32L412xx and STM32L422xx only : Enable Internal tamper using HAL_RTCEx_SetInternalTampe
  95:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****          setting Interrupt field.
  96:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c **** 
  97:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****    *** Backup Data Registers configuration ***
