1725:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****    (+) Before calling any tamper or internal tamper function, you have to call first
1726:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****        HAL_RTC_Init() function.
1727:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****    (+) In that ine you can select to output tamper event on RTC pin.
1728:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
1729:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****    (+) Enable the Tamper and configure the Tamper filter count, trigger Edge
1730:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****        or Level according to the Tamper filter (if equal to 0 Edge else Level)
1731:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****        value, sampling frequency, NoErase, MaskFlag, precharge or discharge and
1732:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****        Pull-UP, timestamp using the HAL_RTCEx_SetTamper() function.
1733:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****        You can configure Tamper with interrupt mode using HAL_RTCEx_SetTamper_IT() function.
1734:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****    (+) The default configuration of the Tamper erases the backup registers. To avoid
1735:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****        erase, enable the NoErase field on the TAMP_TAMPCR register.
1736:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****   [..]
1737:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****    (+) Enable Internal Tamper and configure it with interrupt, timestamp using
1738:Drivers/STM32L4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l4xx_hal_rtc_ex.c ****        the HAL_RTCEx_SetInternalTamper() function.
